      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.formTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 2.3,
      "position": [
        368,
        736
      ],
      "id": "7650a192-0693-41a3-b011-9468d3ad6d2a",
      "name": "Social Post Generator Form",
      "webhookId": "04279444-0778-4634-bc58-3782bb6f04d1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Using the following story data and brand voice guidelines, generate social media posts for multiple platforms.\nUse the Title, Description, internalLink, Image.\n\n**Brand Voice Guidelines:**\nUse the \"Brand Voice Guidelines\" and target audience in creating social media posts. Start with an interesting \"hook\".\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Task Definition\nFor each story provided, generate:\n- 7 platforms: Instagram, Twitter (X), BlueSky, Facebook, LinkedIn, Threads, Pinterest\n- {{ $('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1}} unique variants per platform\n- Each story should therefore produce exactly {{ (7 * ($('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1)) }} posts (7 platforms × {{ $('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1}} variants)\n\n2. Follow platform-specific best practices:\n{{ $('Platform Instructions in Plain Text').item.json.textInstructions }}\n\n\n3. Incorporate the brand voice guidelines in tone, style, and messaging\n\n4. Include the story internal link naturally in each post. Important: All CTAs and links should link to the newsletter issue URL at https://theintersect.art using the internalLink provided\n\n5. Ensure each variant is unique and optimized for its platform\n\n6. Focus the content on my take: {{ $json['My Take'] }}\n\nIMPORTANT RULES:\n- Output ONLY the JSON object - nothing else\n- Output ALL {{ (7 * ($('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1)) }} posts, {{ $('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1}} variants per platform\n- Do NOT add markdown code blocks or backticks\n- Do NOT add explanatory text before or after the JSON\n- Ensure the JSON is valid and parseable\n- Each post must include: storyTitle, platform, variant ({{ $('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1 }}), postText, imageUrl, internalLink\n\n**<Story Data>:**\nTitle: {{ $json.Title }}\nDescription: {{ $json['Content/Summary'] }}\nInternal_Link: {{ $('Split Out1').item.json.internalLink }}\nImage: {{ $json['Featured Image'][0].url }}\noriginalLink: {{ $('Split Out1').item.json.originalLink }}\nMy Take: {{ $json['My Take'] }}\n</Story Data>\n\n<Brand Voice Guidelines>\n- About the Brand: {{ $('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand Description'] }}\n- Brand Voice: {{ $('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand Voice Guidelines'] }}\n- Target Audiences: {{ $('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Target Audiences'] }}\n</Brand Voice Guidelines>\n\n=== TOKEN BUDGET AWARENESS ===\nYou have a maximum of 8000 tokens for your complete response. \nBudget approximately {{ Math.round(500 / ($('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1)) }}-{{ Math.round(600 / ($('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1)) }} tokens per platform variant (7 platforms × {{ $('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1 }} variants = {{ (7 * ($('Workflow Configuration').item.json['Brand variantsPerStory'] || 1)) }} total posts).\n\nTo stay within limits:\n- Keep Instagram posts under 300 characters (not the 2,200 max)\n- Twitter posts must be under 280 characters\n- LinkedIn posts should be 400-600 characters (not the 3,000 max)\n- Be punchy and concise across all platforms\n\nQuality over quantity. Every word must earn its place.\n=== END TOKEN BUDGET AWARENESS ===\n\n=== OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS ===\nImportant: Your output must be in the following JSON format:\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"posts\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"storyTitle\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n          \"platform\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n          \"variant\": { \"type\": \"integer\" },\n          \"postText\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n          \"imageUrl\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n          \"originalLink\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n          \"internalLink\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"storyTitle\",\n          \"platform\",\n          \"variant\",\n          \"postText\",\n          \"imageUrl\",\n          \"originalLink\",\n          \"internalLink\"\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\"posts\"]\n}\n\n=== END OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS ===\n\n\n\nGenerate ALL posts now.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are an expert social media content creator for the Intersect of Art and Tech newsletter. Your task is to transform newsletter stories into engaging platform-specific posts while maintaining the brand's voice and guidelines. \n\n\n=== WRITING STYLE REQUIREMENTS ===\n\nCRITICAL: You are writing social media posts for real humans. Write naturally and avoid ALL AI-generated clichés.\n\nBANNED WORDS & PHRASES (Never use ANY of these):\n• \"delve\" / \"dive into\" / \"deep dive\"\n• \"unlock\" / \"unleash\" / \"unpack\"\n• \"elevate\" / \"enhance\" / \"empower\"\n• \"revolutionize\" / \"game-changer\" / \"disrupt\"\n• \"navigate\" / \"embark\" / \"journey\"\n• \"landscape\" / \"realm\" / \"sphere\" / \"arena\"\n• \"beacon\" / \"resonate\" / \"testament\"\n• \"ever-evolving\" / \"fast-paced\" / \"dynamic\"\n• \"cutting-edge\" / \"state-of-the-art\"\n• \"It's not just...\" / \"It's about more than...\"\n• \"In today's [X] world/landscape...\"\n• \"Let's face it...\" / \"At the end of the day...\"\n• \"turbocharge\" / \"supercharge\"\n\nBANNED CONCEPTS (Avoid these ideas entirely):\n• Don't replace \"elevate\" with \"enhance\" - both are clichés\n• Don't replace \"ever-changing landscape\" with \"fast-paced world\" - still cliché\n• Avoid transformation/journey/evolution metaphors\n• Skip vague \"empowerment\" language\n• Don't end posts with rhetorical questions\n\nWRITE LIKE A REAL PERSON:\n✓ Use simple, direct language\n✓ Mix short and long sentences naturally\n✓ Lead with specifics, not abstractions\n✓ Use concrete examples over general concepts\n✓ Sound conversational, not corporate\n✓ Be opinionated when appropriate\n✓ Use natural transitions (avoid \"moreover,\" \"furthermore,\" \"indeed\")\n\nPLATFORM TONE:\n• Instagram: Visual-first, casual, emoji-friendly\n• Twitter/X: Punchy, direct, conversation-starter\n• LinkedIn: Professional but not stiff, data-driven\n• Facebook: Casual, community-focused\n• Threads: Conversational, thread-worthy\n• BlueSky: Authentic, less corporate\n• Pinterest: Inspirational, actionable, search-optimized\n\nSELF-CHECK:\nBefore finalizing each post:\n1. Would a real person actually say this?\n2. Is this specific to the content or generic filler?\n3. Did I avoid ALL banned words and concepts?\n4. Does it sound authentic or like corporate jargon?\n\nIf you use ANY banned phrase, rewrite that post completely.\n\n=== END STYLE REQUIREMENTS ==="
        }
      },
